and used in further redirection without validation:
Code 279 Bytes
1InfaAutoLogin.authenticateUser(response.id, finalPageURL, {
2	callback:function(responseMap) {
3		if(responseMap['status'] === 'success') {
4			document.location = responseMap['location'];
5		}
6		else {
7			sessionStorage.setItem('autoLoginType', responseMap['statusMsg']);
8		}
9	}
10});
This means an attacker can put JS links there, which will cause script execution in the victim's browser:
Log into your Informatica Network account
Go to https://network.informatica.com/login!input.jspa?referer=javascript:alert(document.domain)
